---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Morocco Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/morocco/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Spain for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/spain' },
  { title: 'Portugal for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/portugal' },
  { title: 'Egypt for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/egypt' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'moroccoFit', header: 'Morocco Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MAD$4,500-6,430/mo', moroccoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MAD$5,265-7,520/mo', moroccoFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MAD$4,050-5,785/mo', moroccoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MAD$3,765-5,380/mo', moroccoFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Wafa, Saham)', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'MAD$800-2,000/mo', moroccoFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MAD$4,050-6,430', annual: 'MAD$48.6K-77.2K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MAD$5,555-8,570', annual: 'MAD$66.7K-102.8K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MAD$7,470-11,505', annual: 'MAD$89.6K-138.1K' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'MAD$300-800/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'MAD$1,500-4,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Morocco 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Morocco. Marrakech riads, Atlantic beaches, French accessibility, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Morocco"
  subheadline="Morocco offers exotic medinas, Marrakech charm, Atlantic beaches, French language accessibility, and close proximity to Europe—North Africa's premier retirement destination."
  heroImage="/images/countries/morocco-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Morocco</h2>
  <p>
    Morocco offers exotic medinas, Marrakech's vibrant culture, Atlantic and Mediterranean beaches, French language accessibility, and close proximity to Europe. For French-speaking retirees seeking exotic experience with European accessibility, Morocco delivers North African charm at moderate cost.
  </p>

  <p>
    Marrakech is the expat favorite with riad living and culture. Casablanca has best healthcare. Tangier offers European proximity. Essaouira and Agadir have beach lifestyles. Fes provides authentic medina experience. Most choose Marrakech or coast; Casablanca for healthcare.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good private; improving; Spain backup</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic; French widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MAD$12,000-25,000/month (~$1,200-2,500 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean/Atlantic; pleasant</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Exotic; accessible; culturally rich</li>
      <li><strong>Europe proximity:</strong> Spain 14km across strait</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Morocco Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Morocco has good private healthcare—Clinique Dar Salam and private hospitals in Casablanca/Rabat provide modern care. Many doctors trained in France. Public system basic. Complex cases may go to Spain (14km across strait) or France. Growing medical tourism destination.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare affordable and improving. French-speaking doctors make communication easy. International insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage. Spain provides excellent European backup.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Spain Backup Available</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Spain is just 14km across Strait of Gibraltar. Malaga and Madrid provide EU-standard healthcare. Include Spain/Europe in insurance coverage. Local private care handles most needs; Spain provides easy backup for complex conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Morocco has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Entry</h3>
  <p>
    90 days visa-free for most Western nationalities. Good for exploration.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Extensions possible beyond 90 days. Border runs common for extended stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Card (Carte de Séjour)</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 90 days. Various categories including retirement. Renewable annually.
  </p>

  <h3>Property Ownership</h3>
  <p>
    Foreigners can buy property. Helps with residence applications.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Morocco:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Regional:</strong> Spain/Europe coverage helpful</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Morocco</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Spain/Europe coverage recommended. Local private care handles most needs. European backup easily accessible. Good combination of exotic living with European medical security nearby.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Morocco, Europe coverage beneficial:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Morocco</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Europe/MENA network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Spain access:</strong> EU healthcare 14km away</li>
    <li><strong>French support:</strong> Language accessible</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Morocco retirement.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Morocco (MAD ~10 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Casablanca network:</strong> Best local hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Europe network:</strong> Use Spain for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> MENA focused options</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: French Marrakech Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,500/month pension. Residence card. Marrakech riad.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with France coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MAD$5,000/month (~$500). Exotic living; French backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Coast Retiree, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,200/month pension. Residence card. Essaouira.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with UK and Spain coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MAD$6,000/month (~$600). Beach lifestyle; European backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: American Explorer, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month pension. Tourist rotation. Fes/Tangier.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with comprehensive coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MAD$4,200/month (~$420). Cultural immersion; global backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need French?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very helpful—French widely spoken in business, healthcare, tourism. Arabic is official but French is de facto second language. English growing but French opens more doors. Healthcare easily accessible in French.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Morocco safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—one of Africa's safest countries. Tourist areas well-managed. Low violent crime. Hassle in medinas (touts, guides) but not dangerous. Women travelers take normal precautions. Overall safe destination.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's Marrakech like for expats?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Large expat community—riads, restaurants, culture. Vibrant, colorful, sometimes overwhelming. Hot in summer. Active social scene. Many renovated riads available. More exotic than coastal towns. Popular for good reason.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How accessible is Spain?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very accessible—14km across Strait of Gibraltar. Ferry from Tangier to Spain. Flights from Marrakech/Casablanca to Spanish cities. Easy weekend trips. EU healthcare backup readily available.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Morocco coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Morocco authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
